{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_40","type":"agent_message","text":"The second run confirms the pattern: it’s the Jackson “optional handler” block activating too broadly under this GraalVM, not just one bad class. I’m restoring more specific conditions for those optional Jackson handlers so the metadata still exists when the relevant SQL/XML/DOM types are actually used, but it won’t poison unrelated builds like this OCI test."}}
