{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_59","type":"agent_message","text":"The owner test exposed the actual tradeoff: dropping the SQL deserializer entries fixes OCI by removing functionality that `jackson-databind` genuinely needs. The next attempt is to restore those two entries using the older `allDeclaredConstructors` form instead of the newer explicit `methods` form, which is the likely part GraalVM 25 is choking on during the OCI image build."}}
