 Focus on validating the Java runtime fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:11:The PR number or URL can be passed as an optional argument (for example, `1234`, `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pull/1234`). If the user says \"review this PR\" without an argument, infer the PR from the surrounding conversation or `gh pr status`; only ask the user when it cannot be inferred. Use `gh pr view <pr>`, `gh pr diff <pr>`, and `gh pr checks <pr>` against the resolved PR throughout the workflow below.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:23:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:36:     - `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<new-version>/reachability-metadata.json`\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:41:   - Treat a new `reachability-metadata.json` for the tested version as normal for this label, including `{}` when validation and stats are coherent.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:42:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `build.gradle`, `gradle.properties`, `settings.gradle`, and `user-code-filter.json` as normal when they live under the target version's test directory.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:45:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:118:- For legacy metadata files: say that metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json` and ask for old config files such as `reflect-config.json` or `resource-config.json` to be replaced.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/PopulateArtifactURLsTests.java:229:                    \"allowed-packages\": [\n./forge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:232:    reach_json = os.path.join(metadata_dir, \"reachability-metadata.json\")\n./forge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:275:        \"reachability-metadata.json\",\n./forge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:482:    # Determine metadata_file path (either reachability-metadata.json or the metadata dir)\n./forge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:484:    reach_json = os.path.join(repo_path, \"metadata\", package, artifact, metadata_version, \"reachability-metadata.json\")\n./build.gradle:112:    String outputFileName = \"graalvm-reachability-metadata-${project.version}.zip\"\n./build.gradle:601:        // Revert tests directory changes (including build.gradle and user-code-filter.json)\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/GenerateDependencyGraphTask.java:56:    private static final String USER_AGENT = \"graalvm-reachability-metadata/GenerateDependencyGraphTask (+https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata)\";\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/ValidateLibraryStatsTaskTests.java:684:                    \"allowed-packages\": [\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/ValidateLibraryStatsTaskTests.java:744:                      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/%s/%s/%s/reachability-metadata.json\",\n./forge/unassign_issues.py:22:REPO = \"oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata\"\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `library-new-request` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that adds metadata and tests for a new library, including PRs titled like `[GenAI] Add support for com.fasterxml:classmate:1.5.1 using gpt-5.4`. Focus on catching scaffold-only tests, version-pinned or package-bypassing tests, and PRs that push more than one library.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:11:The PR number or URL can be passed as an optional argument (for example, `1234`, `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pull/1234`). If the user says \"review this PR\" without an argument, infer the PR from the surrounding conversation (for example, an open review tab, a PR URL mentioned earlier, or the current branch's PR from `gh pr status`); only ask the user when it cannot be inferred. Use `gh pr view <pr>`, `gh pr diff <pr>`, and `gh pr checks <pr>` against the resolved PR throughout the workflow below.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:25:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:38:     - `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/reachability-metadata.json`\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. New-library metadata must be provided through `reachability-metadata.json`, including any test-only metadata under `tests/src/**`.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:56:   - Do not read, list, or reason from individual entries inside `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:58:   - Treat `reachability-metadata.json` containing `{}` as acceptable when the rest of the PR is coherent and validation passes.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:64:   - If the PR reports zero dynamic-access calls and `reachability-metadata.json` is `{}`, that is acceptable as long as the test is library-specific and the scope is otherwise correct.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:104:- For legacy metadata files: say that metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json` and ask for old config files such as `reflect-config.json` or `resource-config.json` to be replaced.\n./forge/docs/e2e.md:67:  --reachability-metadata-path .. \\\n./forge/docs/e2e.md:139:  --reachability-metadata-path <repo> \\\n./forge/docs/e2e.md:151:  --reachability-metadata-path <repo> \\\n./forge/docs/e2e.md:167:  --reachability-metadata-path <repo> \\\n./forge/docs/e2e.md:232:  --reachability-metadata-path <repo> \\\n./settings.gradle:15:rootProject.name = \"reachability-metadata\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/native_image_artifact.py:303:    for dependency in pom_metadata.dependencies:\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:35:                    \"allowed-packages\": [\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:62:                    \"allowed-packages\": [\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:106:                    \"allowed-packages\": [\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:135:                    \"allowed-packages\": [\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:13:[`oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata`](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata)\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:99:| **Reachability repo** | Local checkout or worktree of `oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata`. The build and metadata-generation Gradle tasks run inside it. The parent checkout of `forge/` is used by default. |\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:106:| **Post-generation intervention** | The built-in recovery sequence the workflow base class runs when the post-iteration `./gradlew test` still fails during finalization. It is a fixed Codex-then-Pi lane, not a pluggable registry and not selected per strategy: a Codex metadata fix runs first (using the `fix-missing-reachability-metadata` skill, pinned to the run's GraalVM); only if that does not recover does Pi remove the offending failing tests as a last resort. When recovery makes the post-generation test pass, the run reports `SUCCESS_WITH_INTERVENTION_STATUS` and the intervention record (stage, intervention file, analysis) is saved for the run metrics and PR body. The base class runs this lane once per GraalVM test lane (current defaults and `future-defaults-all` on the latest GraalVM, plus current defaults on the GraalVM 25 toolchain). |\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:137:- `--reachability-metadata-path` — overrides default reachability-repo clone.\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:181:  `graalvm-reachability-metadata` checkout or worktree, not in a copied\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:276:`allowed-packages`, applies and checks style, regenerates library stats, and\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:2:name: fix-missing-reachability-metadata\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:6:# Fix missing reachability metadata entries in the reachability-metadata.json\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:20:   - Copy the suggested JSON entry for the missing type into the corresponding section of the reachability-metadata.\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:22:   - Write to `metadata/<library-specific-metadata-directory>/reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:47:add the following to the 'reflection' section of reachability-metadata.json:\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/ChangedMetadataTestMatrixTests.java:214:        Files.writeString(projectDir.resolve(\"metadata/com.example/demo/\" + version + \"/reachability-metadata.json\"), json);\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/SplitTestOnlyMetadataTask.java:34: * test-resources reachability-metadata.json.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/SplitTestOnlyMetadataTask.java:41:    private static final String REACHABILITY_METADATA_FILE = \"reachability-metadata.json\";\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:7:This repo contains Python scripts and AI-powered pipelines to automate maintenance of the oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata repository (§FS-forge-issue-resolution-goal):\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:19:Forge is located inside `graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge`. The parent checkout is the default reachability repository, and successful run metrics are written under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/execution-metrics.json`. Top-level automation still creates one detached metadata-repo worktree per issue run; the run's pending metrics root is the same worktree's `forge/` directory (§WF-forge-workflow-drivers, §FS-durable-generation-logs).\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:23:- Local clone of https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:46:- Create/update the versioned test module in reachability-metadata.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:55:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:65:- `--reachability-metadata-path`: optional path to a graalvm-reachability-metadata worktree. If omitted, the parent checkout is used.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:74:  --reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata \\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:84:- Runs Gradle tasks inside the reachability-metadata repo (`./gradlew ...`).\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:102:  [--reachability-metadata-path /path/to/graalvm-reachability-metadata] \\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:111:- `--reachability-metadata-path`: optional path to a graalvm-reachability-metadata worktree. If omitted, the parent checkout is used.\n./